Tamika van As is the pride and joy of Bonteheuwel. She learnt to skate at just four years old and has been mastering her craft ever since. She's just won a prestigious title at the South African National Figure Skating Championship. Tanya Nefdt reports. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - She's only eight, but cuts a perfect eight on the ice. Tamika van As is the pride and joy of Bonteheuwel. She learnt to skate at just 4-years-old and has been mastering her craft ever since. Her hard work and commitment are now paying off. She's just won a prestigious title at the South African National Figure Skating Championship. * eNCA's Tanya Nefdt reports.